  <xs:element name="word-lexicons" type="word-lexicons">
    <xs:annotation>
      <xs:documentation>
        A list of word lexicons.  Each lexicon is defined by its collation uri.
      </xs:documentation>
      <xs:appinfo>
        <admin:hr/>
        <admin:help xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
          <span class="help-text"><span style="color:#800000">word 
          lexicons</span> specifies the word lexicons to keep or to add for 
          this configuration.  You can have multiple word lexicons in a
          database or a field,
          each with different collations.  To add a new lexicon, enter the
          collation for the lexicon in the <code>[add]</code> box (for
          example, <code>http://marklogic.com/collation/</code> for the
          UCA Root Collation, which is a sensible collation for many 
          applications).  To remove 
          a lexicon, uncheck the <code>[keep]</code> box for the lexicon 
          you want to remove.  The specified collation is used to order  
          the words in the lexicon.   Each lexicon contains a list of unique 
          words in the database or field, where uniqueness is 
          determined based on the collation chosen.  Typically, the specified 
          collation is case-sensitive and diacritic-sensitive so that 
          there are different entries for <code>Ford</code> and 
          <code>ford</code>.  Also speeds up wildcard searches. Works in 
	  combination with any other available wildcard indexes to improve 
	  search index resolution and performance. When used in conjunction 
	  with the <span style="color:#800000">three character search</span>
	  index, improves wildcard index resolution and speeds up wildcard 
	  searches.
          </span>
        </admin:help>

      </xs:appinfo>
    </xs:annotation>
  </xs:element>

  <xs:element name="word-lexicon" type="collation">
