      <xs:appinfo>
        <admin:help xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
          <span class="help-text"><span style="color:#800000">word 
          lexicon</span> specifies whether a lexicon of words in the
          database should be created using a specific collation for ordering.  
          The lexicon contains a list of unique
          words in the database, where uniqueness is according to the collation
          chosen.  Usually a collation will be
          case-sensitive and diacritic-sensitive so that there is a different
          entry for <code>Ford</code> and 
	  <code>ford</code>.  Also speeds up wildcard searches. Works in 
	  combination with any other available wildcard indexes to improve 
	  search index resolution and performance. When used in conjunction 
	  with the <span style="color:#800000">three character search</span>
	  index, improves wildcard index resolution and speeds up wildcard 
	  searches.
          </span>
        </admin:help>
      </xs:appinfo>
    </xs:annotation>
  </xs:element>

