          <span style="color:#800000">excludes</span> pages 
          to include or exclude elements in the word query 
          configuration (the weight and attribute options do not appear in the
          <span style="color:#800000">excludes</span> page):</span></p>
        </admin:help>
        <admin:help xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <p><span class="help-text">The following are the 
          options for the <span style="color:#800000">includes</span> and 
          <span style="color:#800000">excludes</span> pages 
          to include or exclude elements in the field  
          configuration (the weight and attribute options do not appear in the
          <span style="color:#800000">excludes</span> page):</span></p>
        </admin:help>
        <admin:help xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
          <hr class="control-line" size="1"/>
          <span class="help-text"><p>Buttons and Tabs:</p></span>
          <ul>
	    <li><span class="help-text">Use the 
            <span style="color:#800000">Summary</span> tab to get a high
	    level view of the fields configured in this database.
	    Click on a field name to go to the detailed configuration
